        This Data Scientist role in Marathon will be responsible for modeling complex engineering and operational problems, discovering insights and identifying opportunities through the use of statistical, algorithmic, mining and visualization techniques. In addition to advanced analytic skills, this role will also be proficient at integrating and preparing large, varied datasets including time series data, designing specialized database and computing environments, and communicating results.
        The role will work closely with engineers, geo-scientists, project/program managers, and IT teams to turn oil & gas data into critical information and knowledge that can be used to make sound business decisions. Other responsibilities include providing data that is clean and reliable.
        The role will require a creative thinker who will propose innovative ways to look at problems by using data mining approaches on the set of information available, and validate findings using an experimental and iterative approach.
        The successful candidate will need to be able to present back their findings to the business by focusing on the specific business value while exposing their assumptions and validation work in a way that can be easily understood by the business stakeholders.
        This role requires a combination of business focus, strong analytical and problem solving skills and programming knowledge to be able to quickly cycle hypothesis through the discovery phase of the project. Excellent written and communications skills to report back the findings in a clear, structured manner are required.
        Essential Functions:
        * Focusing on business value of providing solutions - adapt statistical methods to solve specific engineering problems
        * Collaborate with geoscientist, drilling and reservoir engineers in data extraction transform & load, visualization, statistical analysis, predictive modelling and data science concepts
        * Follow established project methodology and strong quality assurance for delivery to scope and requirements
        * Report results of analyses, including information in the form of graphs, charts, and tables to all levels in Marathon
        * Evaluate the statistical methods and procedures used to obtain data in order to ensure validity, applicability, efficiency, and accuracy.
